1. **`_max_size`**: You can adjust this limit according to your needs. It defines how many items the cache can hold before eviction starts.

2. **`store` Method**: When a new item is added, it checks if the cache size has reached the maximum limit. If it has, it removes the least recently used item (based on the `access_time`).

3. **`least_recently_used`**: This line finds the item in the cache that was accessed the longest time ago and removes it.

This approach should help you manage the cache size without needing a major rewrite of your application. However, keep in mind that LRU is a simple eviction policy and may not be optimal for all use cases. Depending on your application's access patterns, you might need a more sophisticated caching strategy.

